To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Freedom of Information Act, I hereby request the following records:

The subject of this request is Christine Fay Wright, who is known to have been originally admitted to the Pennsylvania Bar through reciprocity on May 9, 1988. Pursuant to the Right to Know Law ("RTKL"), we are requesting that you produce information regarding the original state of Christine Fay Wright's bar admission, or the state of admission to practice law which the Commonwealth of Pennsylvania based the grant of license for Ms. Wright to practice law in the Commonwealth of Pennsylvania. We also seek information on Ms. Wright's current status to practice law in the Commonwealth of Pennsylvania. Additionally, if Christine F. Wright does not have an active current license to practice law in the Commonwealth, we request information as to why Ms. Wright's license is no longer active.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 20 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Law Office of William Igbokwe
